{"session_id":"svc-1777981503350928792","seq":0,"type":"session.start","ts":"2026-05-05T11:45:07.456794901Z","data":{"provider":"","model":"gpt-5.4-mini","resolved_harness":"codex","harness_source":"auto_route","resolved_model":"gpt-5.4-mini","work_dir":"/tmp/ddx-exec-wt/.execute-bead-wt-ddx-eccc6efb-20260505T114501-983446fb","max_iterations":0,"prompt":"\u003cexecute-bead\u003e\n  \u003cbead id=\"ddx-eccc6efb\"\u003e\n    \u003ctitle\u003eADR-022 step 7: server-spawn path migration (workers.go → exec ddx work)\u003c/title\u003e\n    \u003cdescription\u003e\nPROBLEM\u0026#xA;ADR-022 step 7 requires migrating from in-process agent execution to a server-spawn model (workers spawned by the server, not by the CLI directly). The current execute-loop launch path uses cli/internal/server/workers.go handleStartExecuteLoopWorker to start a worker subprocess, but this handler may not properly validate all execution parameters or follow the unified ExecuteLoopSpec lifecycle (ApplyDefaults → Validate → StartExecuteLoop).\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;ROOT CAUSE\u0026#xA;- cli/internal/server/workers.go handleStartExecuteLoopWorker (exact line to be confirmed after ddx-89a9c305 lands): the current server-spawn path constructs CLIOverrides and ExecuteBeadLoopRuntime manually rather than going through ApplyDefaults → Validate → StartExecuteLoop with a unified spec.\u0026#xA;- triage:needs-investigation label was added because the exact wiring was unclear at filing time. Investigation findings: the server-spawn handler calls StartExecuteLoop via the workers subsystem, but intermediate struct construction (before ddx-89a9c305 unifies the spec) may drop fields.\u0026#xA;- The server binary is the one that actually execs \u0026#39;ddx work\u0026#39;; the subprocess inherits from server-resolved settings, not from a fully validated ExecuteLoopSpec.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;PROPOSED FIX\u0026#xA;- Confirm handleStartExecuteLoopWorker in cli/internal/server/workers.go validates through ApplyDefaults → Validate before calling StartExecuteLoop.\u0026#xA;- If gaps exist: wire the unified ExecuteLoopSpec (from ddx-89a9c305) into the spawn path.\u0026#xA;- Verify the spawned \u0026#39;ddx work\u0026#39; subprocess receives all spec fields (MaxCostUSD, RequestTimeout, MinPower, MaxPower, OpaquePassthrough, FromRev) via the exec args or a spec file.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;NON-SCOPE\u0026#xA;- Changes to the exec\u0026#39;d ddx work subprocess behavior (that\u0026#39;s C10 / ddx-f9acb86d).\u0026#xA;- REST/GraphQL request decoding (those are ddx-da9e9491 and ddx-ce1d6309).\n    \u003c/description\u003e\n    \u003cacceptance\u003e\n1. cli/internal/server/workers.go handleStartExecuteLoopWorker confirmed to route through ApplyDefaults → Validate → StartExecuteLoop before spawning.\u0026#xA;2. Spawned \u0026#39;ddx work\u0026#39; subprocess receives MaxCostUSD, RequestTimeout, MinPower, MaxPower, OpaquePassthrough, and FromRev.\u0026#xA;3. TestServerSpawnWorker_ExecsDdxWork verifies the server correctly execs ddx work with the resolved spec.\u0026#xA;4. TestServerSpawnWorker_HonorsAllSpecFields verifies all ExecuteLoopSpec fields reach the subprocess.\u0026#xA;5. cd cli \u0026amp;\u0026amp; go test ./internal/server/... green.\u0026#xA;6. lefthook run pre-commit passes.\n    \u003c/acceptance\u003e\n    \u003cnotes\u003e\nREVIEW:BLOCK\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Diff contains only execution evidence files (manifest.json, result.json) — no code changes to workers.go, no struct deletion, no test updates, no end-to-end test. None of ACs 1-6 are implemented; the attempt explicitly declined with a no_changes/needs-investigation rationale requesting decomposition.\n    \u003c/notes\u003e\n    \u003clabels\u003ephase:2, area:server, kind:refactor, adr:022, triage:needs-investigation\u003c/labels\u003e\n    \u003cmetadata parent=\"ddx-d7aca866\" base-rev=\"41290bd529bdc76e856830628e850e874f240273\" bundle=\".ddx/executions/20260505T114501-983446fb\"/\u003e\n  \u003c/bead\u003e\n  \u003cgoverning\u003e\n    \u003cnote\u003eNo governing references were pre-resolved. The bead description above is the primary contract. If it names files, specs, or prior beads, read those before editing. Ground decisions in what is already in the repository; do not guess.\u003c/note\u003e\n  \u003c/governing\u003e\n  \u003cinstructions\u003e\nYou are executing one bead inside an isolated DDx execution worktree. The bead\u0026#39;s \u0026lt;description\u0026gt; and \u0026lt;acceptance\u0026gt; are the completion contract — every AC must be provably satisfied by a specific code, test, or file you can point to after your commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Step 0: size check\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;The bead is too big when any of these holds:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- More than ~6 ACs spanning unrelated subsystems.\u0026#xA;- AC mixes design, implementation, integration tests, and docs as separate top-level deliverables.\u0026#xA;- Description names multiple feature-sized sub-pieces.\u0026#xA;- More than ~500 lines across more than ~5 files in unrelated packages.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If too big, decompose — do not attempt the work:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;1. `ddx bead create` for each child slice (focused title, description, AC; copy parent\u0026#39;s labels and spec-id).\u0026#xA;2. `ddx bead dep add \u0026lt;child-id\u0026gt; \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt;` to record edges.\u0026#xA;3. `ddx bead update \u0026lt;parent-id\u0026gt; --notes \u0026#39;decomposed into \u0026lt;child-ids\u0026gt;\u0026#39;` so the decomposition is visible.\u0026#xA;4. Write `.ddx/executions/20260505T114501-983446fb/no_changes_rationale.txt` listing each child ID and slice, then stop.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;A clean decomposition is a successful attempt. Do not mix partial implementation with decomposition.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## How to work\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- Read first. If the bead names files, specs, or prior beads, read them before editing — do not guess.\u0026#xA;- Cross-reference each AC against concrete evidence (test name, file path, function) before committing. If you cannot point at it, it is not done.\u0026#xA;- Run the project\u0026#39;s test and lint commands before committing. **Do not commit red code** — fix failures first.\u0026#xA;- Stage with `git add \u0026lt;specific-paths\u0026gt;`; never `git add -A` (the worktree may have unrelated WIP).\u0026#xA;- Commit exactly once when green; conventional-commit subject ending with `[\u0026lt;bead-id\u0026gt;]`. Stop after the commit.\u0026#xA;- Do not modify files outside the bead\u0026#39;s scope.\u0026#xA;- If you cannot finish, write `.ddx/executions/20260505T114501-983446fb/no_changes_rationale.txt` (what is done, what blocks, what a follow-up needs) before exiting. No commit and no rationale ⇒ DDx records `no_evidence_produced`. A well-justified no_changes beats a bad commit.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## no_changes contract\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;If you write `.ddx/executions/20260505T114501-983446fb/no_changes_rationale.txt`, it MUST carry one of:\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;- `verification_command: \u0026lt;one-line shell command\u0026gt;` — the loop runs it (cwd = project root, 60s); exit 0 closes the bead, non-zero rejects.\u0026#xA;- `status: needs_investigation` + `reason: \u0026lt;why\u0026gt;` — bead stays open for triage.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Bare rationales (\u0026#34;nothing to do\u0026#34;) are rejected.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Reports\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;Freestanding artifacts (investigation reports, findings docs) go under `.ddx/executions/20260505T114501-983446fb/` (the per-attempt evidence directory under `.ddx/executions/`). **Never write reports to `/tmp` or any path outside the repository** — out-of-repo paths are invisible to the post-merge reviewer and cause BLOCK on missing evidence. If the bead names a specific in-repo path, use it; else default to `.ddx/executions/20260505T114501-983446fb/\u0026lt;short-name\u0026gt;.md`. Stage and commit the report alongside code.\u0026#xA;\u0026#xA;## Bead overrides project defaults\u0026#xA;\u